import React, { useState } from 'react'

const [username, setUserame] = useState(" ");
const [email, setEmail] = useState(" ");
const [password, setPassword] = useState(" ")
const Login = () => {
    return (
        <>
            <form action="">
                <label htmlFor='name'>Name:</label>
                <input
                    type='text'
                    name='user_name'
                    id='name'
                    placeholder='Username'
                    autoComplete='name'
                    required
                />
                <label htmlFor='email'>Email:</label>
                <input
                    type='email'
                    name='user_email'
                    id='email'
                    placeholder='Email'
                    autoComplete='email'
                    required
                />
                <label htmlFor='email'>Email:</label>
                <input
                    type='email'
                    name='user_email'
                    id='email'
                    placeholder='Email'
                    autoComplete='email'
                    required
                />
            </form>
        </>
    );

}

export default Login
